---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import CallToAction from '../../components/CallToAction.astro';

import governmentHero from '../../assets/government-hero.jpg';
import governmentBuilding from '../../assets/government-building.jpg';
import iaqDashboard from '../../assets/iaq-360-dashboard.png';
---

<Base
  title="Government Facilities"
  description="Air and surface purification plus real-time IAQ 360 monitoring for government buildings and correctional facilities. Helps meet OSHA and EPA obligations."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Government Facilities"
    title="Why air quality matters in government facilities"
    lead="Public buildings carry high occupancy, heavy traffic and strict health and safety obligations — on ageing infrastructure that was never designed for either."
    image={governmentHero}
    imageAlt="Corridor inside a correctional facility"
  />

  <Section>
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.4fr_1fr]">
      <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
        <p>
          Poor indoor air quality within government facilities has a direct impact on the health of employees and
          visitors — and government facilities must also follow strict health and safety regulations enforced by OSHA
          and the EPA. The higher the occupancy and traffic, the more dust, allergens and pollutants in the air. Without
          properly purifying the indoor air, contaminants accumulate quickly.
        </p>
        <p>
          Infrastructure and HVAC systems in older government buildings deteriorate over time, which leads to filters
          not properly circulating clean air. Health issues including Legionnaires' disease, asthma and hypersensitivity
          pneumonitis have been linked to poor indoor air quality and poor ventilation in such facilities.
        </p>
      </div>
      <Image
        src={governmentBuilding}
        alt="Exterior of a government office building"
        widths={[400, 700, 1000]}
        sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 26rem, 100vw"
        class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- The old page titled this section "FUNDING....change copy below" — an editor
       note that shipped to production. Replaced with a real heading. -->
  <Section tone="tint" eyebrow="A two-part approach" title="Purify the air, then prove it">
    <div class="mt-8 grid items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="space-y-5 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
        <p>
          Germ Solutions USA provides the <strong class="font-semibold text-brand-700">Indoor Air Quality Monitoring
          System 360</strong>. This technology enables building administrators to continuously monitor air quality
          within a facility in real time. The proactive approach allows early detection of potential issues and ensures
          prompt action can be taken to maintain a healthy indoor environment.
        </p>
        <p>
          Aerus indoor air purification products are designed to release molecules that actively target and disable
          COVID-19 and other pathogens present in the air and on surfaces. Integrating these systems into existing
          infrastructure creates a safer, healthier environment for everyone who enters the building.
        </p>
        <p>
          The combination of the IAQ 360 testing service and the Aerus purification system results in a safer, healthier
          environment for employees and visitors — while meeting OSHA and EPA regulations.
        </p>
      </div>
      <Image
        src={iaqDashboard}
        alt="IAQ 360 monitoring dashboard showing real-time air quality readings alongside its sensor unit"
        widths={[400, 800, 1400]}
        sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 34rem, 100vw"
        class="rounded-2xl bg-white p-4 shadow-lg"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section>
    <a
      href="/industries/government-facilities/cambria-county"
      class="group grid items-center gap-8 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 transition-all hover:border-brand-300 hover:shadow-lg md:grid-cols-[1fr_1.3fr]"
    >
      <Image
        src={governmentHero}
        alt="Interior of a correctional facility"
        widths={[400, 700]}
        sizes="(min-width: 768px) 22rem, 100vw"
        class="h-full min-h-56 w-full object-cover"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <div class="p-8 md:pr-10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent-500">Case study</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-800 text-balance">
          Lehigh, York &amp; Cambria County correctional facilities
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
          Three Pennsylvania prison facilities found a solution for their poor indoor air quality — with 12 months of
          pathogen testing to prove it.
        </p>
        <span class="mt-5 inline-block font-semibold text-brand-500 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5">
          Read the success story <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </span>
      </div>
    </a>
  </Section>

  <CallToAction
    title="Serving public facilities across Pennsylvania"
    lead="We hold COSTARS, TIPS and PEPPM purchasing contracts. Tell us about your facility and we will take it from there."
  />
</Base>
